# ============================================================
# QUEST CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: quest
scope: quest.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for quest.

## policy_rules
Quest policy constrains:
- who may issue quests
- who may hold or progress quests
- which quest detail may be disclosed
- how completion/failure may be acknowledged
- when quest paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- issuer eligibility must be explicit
- holder/progress scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- completion policy must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public quest summary
- holder-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical quest detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow issue/progress only for valid scope
- allow completion only for valid condition basis
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden objective widening
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If issuer scope,
progress scope,
completion basis,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the quest path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- issuer policy is explicit
- completion policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
